00:38:18.295 --> 00:38:21.062
not including nuclear,
by the year 2030.

00:38:21.062 --> 00:38:23.805
So they want to decommission
all of their nuclear plants

00:38:23.805 --> 00:38:24.305
by 2030.

00:38:24.305 --> 00:38:26.030
And that's a really
ambitious goal.

00:38:26.030 --> 00:38:29.010
Well, what's happenening is,
so companies like Google,

00:38:29.010 --> 00:38:32.505
and the Army, and
Walmart, in Germany,

00:38:32.505 --> 00:38:35.220
who have really bought into
this idea, all of a sudden,

00:38:35.220 --> 00:38:39.140
there's just an extraordinary
amount of innovation profit

00:38:39.140 --> 00:38:42.510
that's coming from it,
savings that has really

00:38:42.510 --> 00:38:45.465
sparked all kinds
of imagination.

00:38:45.465 --> 00:38:46.840
And people who
work for companies

00:38:46.840 --> 00:38:49.942
that are involved in that
report just being happy.

00:38:49.942 --> 00:38:51.400
They actually show
up to work more.

00:38:53.940 --> 00:38:55.780
So it certainly
is possible here.

00:38:55.780 --> 00:38:59.015
And states here that have been
the most progressive, places

00:38:59.015 --> 00:39:02.187
like California,
New Jersey, Ohio,

00:39:02.187 --> 00:39:04.020
have been really
aggressive with this stuff,

00:39:04.020 --> 00:39:06.870
are getting a lot of solar.

00:39:06.870 --> 00:39:09.217
And Germany, I forgot
what the percentage is,

00:39:09.217 --> 00:39:10.800
but I was just reading
this yesterday.

00:39:10.800 --> 00:39:14.900
And I believe it's-- I think
it's almost half of the energy

00:39:14.900 --> 00:39:18.340
is actually owned by
individuals and farmers.

00:39:18.340 --> 00:39:19.959
So that's an
extraordinary model.

00:39:19.959 --> 00:39:21.750
And when that happens,
it can really do it.

00:39:21.750 --> 00:39:25.120
And the other thing is
to put a price on carbon.

00:39:25.120 --> 00:39:28.040
Because right now,
the price we're paying

00:39:28.040 --> 00:39:30.620
doesn't get onto the
accounting sheet.

00:39:30.620 --> 00:39:31.930
So that's all externalized.

00:39:31.930 --> 00:39:33.850
And we have to
internalize those costs

00:39:33.850 --> 00:39:38.830
and pay for what
that really costs.

00:39:38.830 --> 00:39:41.890
AUDIENCE: My dad us like--
he hates solar energy,

00:39:41.890 --> 00:39:42.810
